## 2. TA March
**Frequency:** 1x Daily / 7x Weekly  
**Sets:** 2 | **Reps:** 15

### Setup
Begin lying on your back with your arms resting at your sides, your knees bent and your feet flat on the ground.

### Movement
Tighten your abdominals and slowly raise one of your legs off the floor, keeping your knee bent. Then return to the starting position and repeat with your other leg.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your trunk stiff during the exercise and do not let your low back arch.

---

## 3. Split Stance Single Arm Row with Thoracic Rotation
**Frequency:** 1x Daily / 7x Weekly  
**Sets:** 2 | **Reps:** 15

### Setup
Grab a single handle on a cable machine or with bands. Adjust anchor point so it is about at elbow height. Place opposite foot forward and opposite arm out in front of you.

### Movement
Find neutral pelvis, engage lower abdominals and pull handle focusing on squeezing your shoulder blade back and down while the opposite arm presses forward. As the weight pulls you back to the starting position, pull the opposite arm back. Maintain stillness in your legs and pelvis throughout the exercise and squeeze abs more as you pull the weight toward you.

### Tips
- Breathe out as you pull the weight and inhale as the weight pulls you back to the starting position.
- Keep belly button facing straight ahead as if a laser pointer was aiming at the wall and not moving.

